    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "`current` means here not only blocks are downloaded, but also executed, and all other indices are built. \r\nErigon doesn't process blocks one-by-one. It will exec all blocks first, then built history index for all block, then build next index for all blocks, and next, ... It means this field will become > only when all blocks are processed (not when at least one block processed). https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/eth/stagedsync/README.md\r\n",
